From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 20:15:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Publish Sony speaker interface before hotplug notify.

SetupDiCreateDeviceInterfaceW() creates the fake AudioEndpoint interface,
but Wine's SetupAPI does not mark a newly created interface as linked and
present.  The existing fake-audio enumeration workaround only writes
Control\\Linked when an application later enumerates the interface class.

This leaves a race during Sony controller swaps: mmdevapi can send the
endpoint-added notification while the matching PnP interface is not yet
published.  Spider-Man Remastered sees the MMDevice and its properties, but
does not activate it.  A later physical replug appears to fix the endpoint
because it provokes another full interface enumeration.

For a freshly registered Sony controller speaker, enumerate the render or
capture interface class once before MMDevice_Register() returns.  This uses
the existing SetupAPI fake-audio path to publish the exact new interface
before mmdevapi sends endpoint notifications.  It does not preserve any
state after disconnect or change default-device selection.

---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 20 ++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 7fdfc4325b1..38411f3785a 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1281,8 +1281,24 @@ static void MMDevice_Register(const WCHAR *instguid, const WCHAR *friendly_name,
                 memset(&device_interface_data, 0, sizeof(device_interface_data));
                 device_interface_data.cbSize = sizeof(device_interface_data);
 
-                if (!SetupDiCreateDeviceInterfaceW(device_set, &device_info_data, flow == eRender ? &DEVINTERFACE_AUDIO_RENDER : &DEVINTERFACE_AUDIO_CAPTURE, NULL, 0, &device_interface_data))
-                    WARN("SetupDiCreateDeviceInterfaceW failed.");
+                {
+                    const GUID *interface_class = flow == eRender ?
+                            &DEVINTERFACE_AUDIO_RENDER : &DEVINTERFACE_AUDIO_CAPTURE;
+                    HDEVINFO interface_set;
+
+                    if (!SetupDiCreateDeviceInterfaceW(device_set, &device_info_data,
+                            interface_class, NULL, 0, &device_interface_data))
+                        WARN("SetupDiCreateDeviceInterfaceW failed.");
+                    else if (is_dualsense_device_path(device_path))
+                    {
+                        interface_set = SetupDiGetClassDevsW(interface_class, NULL, NULL,
+                                DIGCF_PRESENT | DIGCF_DEVICEINTERFACE);
+                        if (interface_set == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
+                            WARN("Failed to publish fresh Sony controller speaker interface: %lu.\n", GetLastError());
+                        else
+                            SetupDiDestroyDeviceInfoList(interface_set);
+                    }
+                }
             }
             else
                 WARN("SetupDiCreateDeviceInfoW failed.");
-- 
